        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">01</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">Can veterinarians qualify for Physician/Doctor Loan programs like physicians do?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Generally no. Veterinarians hold the DVM doctoral degree but are NOT typically eligible for Physician/Doctor Loan products at most specialty lenders &mdash; similar contrast to pharmacists. Some specialty lenders extend veterinary-specific products to DVMs but these are less common than Physician Loan extension to NPs/PAs. The optimal mortgage path for veterinarians is Conventional Conforming or Jumbo with proper B3-6-05 IDR-aware DTI treatment for the substantial DVM student loan burden. We don&rsquo;t waste time chasing Physician Loan products that won&rsquo;t accept the DVM credential.</div>
